# FIGMA TO CODE RULES

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + React Router v7 (file-based routing)
- TypeScript 5.8+
- Tailwind CSS v4 + HeroUI v2.8+
- Framer Motion v12+ (animations)
- Valtio v2+ (state management)
- xior v0.7+ (HTTP client)
- Embla Carousel React (sliders)
- react-hot-toast (notifications)
- @mantine/hooks (utility hooks)
- Cloudflare Pages deployment

## Project Structure
```
app/
├── routes/                # File-based routing (flat routes)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # Atomic (HeroUI + custom)
│   ├── sections/         # Composite sections
│   └── layout/           # Header, Footer, Nav
├── lib/
│   ├── api/             # xior API clients
│   ├── store/           # Valtio stores
│   ├── hooks/           # Custom hooks
│   └── utils/           # Ramda utilities
└── styles/              # Tailwind globals
```

## Figma Implementation Rules

### 1. Analysis First
- Take screenshot from Figma
- Extract ALL design tokens: colors (hex), typography (font, size, weight, line-height), spacing (px)
- Identify reusable components
- Note all interactive states (hover, focus, active)
- Check animations/transitions

### 2. Styling - 100% Accuracy Required
**Colors**: Extract exact hex codes from Figma
**Typography**:
- Font family (exact from Figma)
- Font size: px → rem conversion
- Font weight: 300-800
- Line height & letter spacing
**Spacing**: Use Tailwind scale (1 = 4px)
**Borders & Shadows**: Match Figma Inspector exactly

### 3. Component Pattern
```typescript
import { cn } from "~/lib/utils";
import { motion } from "framer-motion";

interface Props {
  // TypeScript types required
}

export function Component({ ...props }: Props) {
  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      className={cn(
        // Layout
        "flex flex-col items-center",
        // Spacing (match Figma exactly)
        "px-6 py-4 gap-4",
        // Typography
        "text-base font-semibold",
        // Colors (exact hex from Figma)
        "bg-white text-gray-900",
        // Effects
        "rounded-lg shadow-lg",
        // Responsive
        "md:flex-row md:px-8 lg:gap-8",
        // Interactive
        "hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300",
        props.className
      )}
    >
      {/* Content */}
    </motion.div>
  );
}
```

### 4. Responsive Breakpoints
- Mobile: < 768px (single column, touch-friendly)
- Tablet: 768px - 1024px (2-column layouts)
- Desktop: ≥ 1024px (full multi-column)

Use: `useMediaQuery` from @mantine/hooks when needed

### 5. Animations (Framer Motion)
```typescript
// Page transitions
const variants = {
  initial: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  animate: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },
  exit: { opacity: 0, y: -20 }
};

// Hover effects
<motion.button
  whileHover={{ scale: 1.05 }}
  whileTap={{ scale: 0.95 }}
/>
```

### 6. State Management (Valtio)
```typescript
import { proxy, useSnapshot } from 'valtio';

export const store = proxy({
  data: [],
  updateData(newData) {
    this.data = newData;
  }
});

// In component
const snap = useSnapshot(store);
```

### 7. API Calls (xior)
```typescript
import xior from 'xior';

const api = xior.create({ baseURL: '/api' });
export const fetchData = () => api.get('/endpoint');
```

### 8. Utilities
- `cn()` from ~/lib/utils for className merging (tailwind-merge + clsx)
- Ramda for functional programming
- js-cookie for cookie management
- query-string for URL params

### 9. UI Components Priority
1. Use HeroUI components as base (Button, Input, Card, Modal, etc.)
2. Extend with Tailwind classes for custom styling
3. Wrap with Framer Motion for animations
4. Match Figma design exactly

### 10. Verification Checklist
- [ ] Visual comparison: screenshot code vs Figma
- [ ] Colors match exactly (use color picker)
- [ ] Typography: font, size, weight, line-height
- [ ] Spacing: padding, margin, gap
- [ ] Responsive: test all breakpoints
- [ ] Interactions: hover, focus, active states work
- [ ] Animations smooth (no janky animations)
- [ ] Performance: lazy loading, optimized images
- [ ] Accessibility: keyboard nav, ARIA labels, contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
- [ ] No console errors

## Critical Rules
⚠️ NEVER approximate - get exact values from Figma Inspector
⚠️ Use React Router v7 patterns (NO react-router-dom imports)
⚠️ Use Valtio for state (NO Redux/Zustand)
⚠️ Use xior for HTTP (NO axios directly)
⚠️ Tailwind CSS v4 with @tailwindcss/vite plugin
⚠️ All animations via Framer Motion
⚠️ TypeScript strict mode - no `any` types
⚠️ Mobile-first responsive design

## Workflow
1. Analyze Figma design thoroughly
2. Extract all design tokens
3. Plan component hierarchy
4. Implement section by section
5. Add animations & interactions
6. Verify against Figma
7. Optimize performance
